  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Percutaneous transluminal angioplasty (PTA) is a minimally invasive procedure for dilating
      blood vessels in the treatment of peripheral artery disease.

      The aim of this registry is to collect prospectively and systematically clinical research
      data from patients undergoing PTA. This registry is an open-end observational study to assess
      the characteristics and outcomes in patients with undergoing PTA.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
